  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6580.44 sitting below the 6608 flip strike in PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and likely buying this dip while providing stabilizing flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6600 (60B+) creates a strong magnetic effect that should cap upside moves, while the negative gamma pocket at 6560 (-24B) represents where dealers would aggressively buy any selloff. The recent regime flip and GEX surge of 236% suggests dealers just shifted positioning significantly, reinforcing the 6560-6608 range as the new trading corridor.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 6600 with limited downside below 6560.",
